;a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:24:\"gutenberg-themes-roundup\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"https://make.wordpress.org/themes/?p=19015\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:363:\"Hello! This is the 25th weekly roundup of theme-related discussions, fixes, and developments in Gutenberg.  Please weigh in on the tickets below — your voice and feedback are welcome!  In progress / Discussions: Discussion: Allow themes to dynamically add CSS class names to the editor wrapper. 26494 Bug: Preset size dropdown includes empty li when [&#8230;]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14:\"Kjell Reigstad\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4697:\"<p>Hello! This is the 25th weekly roundup of theme-related discussions, fixes, and developments in Gutenberg. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Please weigh in on the tickets below — your voice and feedback are welcome! </p>\n\n\n\n<p>In progress / Discussions:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Discussion: Allow themes to dynamically add CSS class names to the editor wrapper. <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/issues/26494\">26494</a></li><li>Bug: Preset size dropdown includes empty li when only custom font sizes are enabled <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/issues/26489\">26489</a></li><li>Bug: Toolbar buttons can inherit the editors text color when active. <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/issues/26462\">26462</a></li><li>Suggestion: Box-layout attribute. <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/issues/26407\">26407</a></li><li>FSE: Rethink how template parts work. <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/issues/26392\">26392</a></li><li>FSE: Automatically enable FSE for block-based themes. <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/pull/26500\">26500</a></li><li>FSE Discussion: Handling of templates and template parts duplicates. <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/issues/26546\">26546</a></li><li>Editor: Try a wider vanilla / default column width. <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/pull/26357\">26357</a></li></ul><p>Merged:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Full-site editor: Add Dropdown to Create Generic Templates. <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/pull/26284\">26284</a></li><li>Query Block: expose initial templates as block variations. <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/pull/26378\">26378</a></li><li>Full-site editor: Add “convert to template part” flow. <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/pull/20445\">20445</a></li><li>Full-site editor: Add RTL support for navigation. <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/pull/26334\">26334</a></li><li>Twenty Twenty-One Blocks was started in the theme experiments repository: <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/theme-experiments/pull/57\">57</a></li><li>Themes now use stylesheet rather than textdomain as their identifier: <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/pull/25995\">25995</a></li><li>Fix allowing FSE themes to live in a subdirectory within the themes directory: <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/pull/26391\">26391</a></li></ul><p>Overview Issues:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Full Site Editing Milestones. <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/issues/24551\">24551</a></li><li>Template Tags in Full Site Editing. <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/issues/22724\">22724</a> </li><li>Tracking and consolidating style attributes for blocks. <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/issues/22700\">22700</a> </li><li>Missing query block functionality. <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/issues/24934\">24934</a></li><li>Query and Loop block tracking: <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/issues/24762\">24762</a></li></ul><p>General Resources:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/labels/%5BFeature%5D%20Full%20Site%20Editing\">GitHub Issues: Full Site Editing</a></li><li><a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/labels/%5BFeature%5D%20Themes\">GitHub  Issues: Themes</a></li><li><a href=\"https://developer.wordpress.org/block-editor/developers/themes/block-based-themes/\">Block-based Themes Reference</a></li><li><a href=\"https://developer.wordpress.org/block-editor/tutorials/block-based-themes/\">Block-based Themes Tutorial</a></li><li><a href=\"https://developer.wordpress.org/block-editor/developers/themes/theme-json/\">Experimental-Themes.json</a></li><li><a href=\"https://make.wordpress.org/themes/2020/07/05/using-the-block-editor-for-theme-parts/\">Using the Block Editor for Theme Parts</a></li><li><a href=\"https://wp.me/p29gdg-4MC\">Printing navigation-block HTML from a legacy menu in themes</a></li></ul><p>Thanks to <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/itsjusteileen/\" class=\"mention\"><span class=\"mentions-prefix\">@</span>itsjusteileen</a>, <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/jffng/\" class=\"mention\"><span class=\"mentions-prefix\">@</span>jffng</a>, <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/joen/\" class=\"mention\"><span class=\"mentions-prefix\">@</span>joen</a>, and <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/scruffian/\" class=\"mention\"><span class=\"mentions-prefix\">@</span>scruffian</a> for help pulling this post together. Please let us know if it was helpful in the comments!</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a